&lt;h1&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Lead Product Manager, CRM&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We&#39;re looking for a strategic and execution-focused Lead Product Manager to own and evolve the CRM and agent tooling platform powering Matic Local, our new retail distribution channel. This is a greenfield opportunity to define a market segment, tailor the product from the ground up, and scale it into a core growth engine for Matic. You&#39;ll partner closely with the Matic Local business lead, engineering, operations, and data to give agents the tools they need to win in local markets.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Candidates must be based in or willing to relocate to Columbus, Ohio.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Define the product vision and roadmap for the CRM and agent tooling platform that powers Matic Local&#39;s agent network.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner directly with the Matic Local business leaders to translate field needs, agent workflows, and distribution dynamics into product requirements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct ongoing user research with agents, loan officers, and referral partners to deeply understand how they work and where friction exists.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead cross-functional teams through discovery, delivery, and iteration of features that improve agent productivity, pipeline visibility, and referral partner engagement.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design and build the onboarding, lead management, and performance tracking experiences agents rely on to produce results.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Define and track success metrics across agent activation, pipeline conversion, referral partner engagement, and overall Matic Local unit economics.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Serve as the connective tissue between the field and the product org, translating what is and isn&#39;t working into a clear, prioritized backlog.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify opportunities to integrate AI and automation into agent workflows to reduce friction and increase throughput.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Requirements&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;7+ years of product management experience, including at least 2 years in a lead or senior role.&lt;/li&gt;
